00:38:03.460 --> 00:38:10.310
And I've always wanted those
qualities to merge in some way.

00:38:10.310 --> 00:38:14.000
But what character traits taught
me was that in order to do that,

00:38:14.000 --> 00:38:17.370
the content of my
books needs to change.

00:38:17.370 --> 00:38:21.120
My texts that I typically set

00:38:21.120 --> 00:38:25.740
in my traditional
typefaces is usually notes

00:38:25.740 --> 00:38:28.800
or an addendum to
some other work.

00:38:28.800 --> 00:38:32.860
And so, I'm trying to
figure out what that means,

00:38:32.860 --> 00:38:36.940
that somehow I need to start
working with texts that allow me

00:38:36.940 --> 00:38:42.510
to experiment more
visually with words,

00:38:42.510 --> 00:38:44.240
rather than having
them separate.

00:38:44.240 --> 00:38:49.050
So I've got a couple ideas
